node.text:
THE NEW TRAILER TO BLACK WIDOW!!!
Oh my goodness. I can’t stop saying “it’s right around the corner..”
I know to a lot of people the date being pushed for the release of this movie multiple times has caused annoyance, but in all honesty I truly believe it was the correct decision. I witnessed SO much hard work going into the making of it and I was only around within the last year of the creation! This film deserves the big screens, it deserves the loud speakers ‘THUD THUD’ when the Marvel logo screams across the screen. It deserves that sensation of watching a Marvel movie alongside other excited fans and movie goers. It deserves its viewers feeling comfortable and safe in their seats. 
It deserves all of it. I’m so excited. I’m so proud. I’m so grateful for Marvel holding out and giving this film the moment it deserves, I know it was a wait... but shit will it be worth it. 
It’s. Right. Around. The. Corner.

#blackwidow #hellyesssss

A true bromance. Last year Nick was performing at 54 Below, singing and playing his life story through songs. As you can hear.. we loved it. 
Nick and Drew were performing their final song, ‘You Matter To Me’ from the musical Waitress, whilst Zach waited in the audience with a headlamp on ready for his cue. 
I’m so happy I captured this. 
The boys in their happy place, on stage singing and laughing, performing love songs to each other. 
So much love. 
I’m sat crouching on the floor in front of Amanda, both of us screaming proudly!

Go on to Spotify and listen to him sing- I promise you you’ll end up beaming.

We lost one of the great ones today. 
My friend Nick Cordero passed this morning, holding hands with all his loved ones. Him and his wife @amandakloots have been fighting extremely hard for 90 days. He caught COVID 19 in March and has been hospitalised ever since despite having no pre-existing health conditions. 

This was him April ‘19! 
In his element. 
On stage whilst commanding the entire audience so intensely, you could have heard a pin drop. 
The ONLY person who can ease so effortlessly from ‘What A Wonderful World’ to Coldplay’s ‘Politik’, all the while singing directly across the room to Amanda. She knew all the words and started head banging the moment she heard Coldplay. Every night. For three nights. 
7 months pregnant!!! 

It is so shocking and devastating to see one of your own come down as hard as he did. Over the last few months I’ve wanted to ask myself every day- what can I do to help? But, instead I’ll ask all of you. What can WE do to help?
We still can. Help the world by continuing to take this virus seriously. Wear your mask, respect others’ space, clean your hands and please be safe. This is far from over. 

Nick, we love you to infinity and beyond. 
Rest In Peace you beautiful, beautiful man.

“I will never forget the constant sound of ventilators and Dr Francesca’s increasingly desperate plea to find beds for patients.” A few weeks back I was asked if I would like to join this powerful piece directed by Sasha Achilli. 
This story follows the painful journey of the incredibly brave Francesca Mangiatrodi, an A&E doctor inside a hospital in the small northern Italian city of Cremona at the heart of the outbreak in Italy. 
With the world opening up bit by bit, with some areas soaring even higher with Covid than before, I find this film even more important to watch and take in. 
Please take a look and please be safe. 
Italy’s Frontline: A Doctor’s Diary airs on BBC 2 and BBC IPlayer on 29th June at 9pm (Sorry forgot to add) 
@sasha_achilli @mongoosedan 
@bbctwo @bbcthisworld

node.text:
My little bunny is 18 today. She’s the little sister I never asked for (haha), but oh my goodness has she made the last 18 years. I remember holding her when she was a bald little thing and understanding what this funny expression my mum had been trying to explain ‘maternal instinct’ finally meant. 
She’s a true force, incredibly loud, sometimes too loud but that’s just her, she’s passionate, she’s the best at wiping tears you didn’t know were coming, she’s so unbelievably talented and I’m so proud of my now not so little baby. 
This birthday especially hurts that I’m not there, SO EVERYONE SEND HER BIRTHDAY LOVE. Love you baby. X

This is my main lady @kella.mcallister. We met at the beginning of prep for Black Widow, when I needed to learn how to be an assassin. Quickly. 
She was with me everyday when I was learning kickboxing from @troystunt and finessing and practising choreo from @jyou10. We would train every morning, alongside other awesome stunt women who just were completely invested and wanted to help. 
She would watch and help me understand anything I was struggling with. Practice until we nailed it. I never thought the relationship between you and your stunty could be quite so wonderful. She encouraged and fought for me on and off set, she trained me for things she knew I could do, (even if I had little faith) and most importantly she was not only excited by the thought BUT wanted me to be involved with how and why Yelena moves the way that she does. To be honest, this was one of the coolest parts of this film. Having this awesome and incredibly talented woman in lock step with me,  helping to achieve what I and everyone else in that room had in mind for Yelena. She’s a champ and I’m so lucky we found each other when we did. I look forward to and hope I get to throw more knives at cardboard boxes with you, dropping from a wire and posing seductively for you, and continuing to learn all I can from you. Thank bunny. You’re a legend.
